  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nNA\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nThe `INFO Ready for Capella` logs will detect if the EE supports the new Capella endpoints, but it doesn't check that the EE is configured to actually fork the network.\r\n\r\nFor example, on Goerli Lighthouse v3.5.1 will log \"Ready for Capella\" with Geth v1.11.2, however the Goerli hardfork is not configured in Geth until v1.11.3.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nIdeally we detect if the EE is properly configured for the fork. If we can't do that, then perhaps we just add some more info to the \"Ready for Capella\" logs to say that you might still need to update your EE.\r\n",
